Happy Tongue Out Tuesday from Sparkle! Many will take one look at her and turn the other way...but if anyone would take a minute to observe her, take another step closer and look past those horribly cropped ears and into those deep chocolate eyes, they will see how she got the name Sparkle. This girl exudes happiness and love. Sparkle does not hold grudges against humans for mutilating her ears or for abandoning her with her uterus protruding from her body. She enjoys every walk, every minute of playtime out of her kennel, every treat and loving touch. You will laugh at her silly antics. Sparkle is one of those dogs that will fill your life with joy. She is not a demanding or high energy dog but is happy with a walk and a bit of playtime with a squeaky toy. She gets along with other dogs too. Sparkle is about 4 years old, 45 lbs and fully vetted. Contact forgottenpetadvocates@yahoo.com

So, happy adoption day to my little brother. I love you but you also get on my nerves sometimes, but I guess that's little brothers for you. - Love, Kobe
